FBIS4-24512 "drchi104_v_94025" FBIS-CHI-94-104 Daily Report 28 May 1994 TAIWAN Foreign Investments Rise in Aviation Industry Foreign Investments Rise in Aviation Industry OW2805082394 Taipei CNA in English 0705 GMT 28 May 94 OW2805082394 Taipei CNA English BFN [By Y. C. Tsai] [Text] Taipei, May 28 (CNA) -- Foreign investors are working to make inroads into the peripheral businesses for the air transportation industry in Taiwan, trade sources said Saturday [28 May]. The sources made the remark after the ministry of economic affairs approved an investment plan by Hong Kong's Alde Burgh Ltd. to open a flight kitchen company here. Alde Burgh is an affiliated firm of the Swire Group, a business conglomerate in the British colony. The project calls for a total investment of NT [new Taiwan)0 $2.27 billion (US$84.07 million), half of which will come from a bank loan. This is the second such project to get the green light here. Earlier this month, the ministry approved a similar investment plan by an American company. The sources forecast that a growing number of foreign enterprises will join domestic air freight peripheral businesses as Taiwan aims to become an Asia-Pacific air transportation center. Moreover, they pointed out, Lockheed Aircraft Corp. of the United States has decided to increase investment in its Taiwan subsidiary by NT$610 million (US$22.59 million) to open a production as well as repair and maintenance center for flight control systems. The capital increment plan has already been approved by the ministry, they added.
